\begin{verbatim}
DerricoEst
\end{verbatim}
D'Errico noise estimation

This method has been proposed by John D'Errico in [1]

\textbf{Fields}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{nothing}

\end{itemize}
\textbf{Reference}

[1] John D'Errico (2023). Estimatenoise, MATLAB Central File Exchange. Retrieved December 7, 2023. (https://www.mathworks.com/matlabcentral/fileexchange/16683-estimatenoise)

\begin{verbatim}
varest(x, method::NoiseEstimation; batch_size = 0, summary = mean)
varest(x; batch_size = 0, summary = mean)
\end{verbatim}
Estimates the noise variance of a signal \texttt{x} using a given method

\textbf{Inputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{x}: Signal


\item \texttt{method}: Noise estimation method

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{BayesianEst}: Bayesian noise estimation (To be implemented)


\item \texttt{GCVEst}: Generalized Cross-Validation (GCV) noise estimation


\item \texttt{LCurveEst}: L-curve noise estimation


\item \texttt{DerricoEst}: D'Errico noise estimation (default)

\end{itemize}

\item \texttt{batch\_size::Int}: Batch size for batch processing (default = 0)


\item \texttt{summary}: Summary function for batch processing (default = mean)

\end{itemize}
\textbf{Output}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{noisevar}: Noise variance - Vector\{Real\}

\end{itemize}
\textbf{Note}

\begin{itemize}
\item varest(x; ...) = varest(x, DerricoEst(); ...)

\end{itemize}

